<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>

<head>
  <% include partials/header %>
  <link href="https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Cormorant+Garamond:wght@300;400;600&family=Karla:wght@300;400;500&display=swap" rel="stylesheet">
  <style>
    :root {
      --gold: #c9963a;
      --gold-light: #e8bc68;
      --deep: #1a0f00;
      --cream: #fdf6ec;
      --muted: #8a7560;
      --text: #3a2810;
    }

    .styled-page {
      background: var(--cream);
      color: var(--text);
      font-family: 'Karla', sans-serif;
      padding-bottom: 40px;
    }

    .page-header {
      text-align: center;
      padding: 40px 24px 36px;
      position: relative;
    }

    .page-header::after {
      content: '';
      display: block;
      width: 60px;
      height: 2px;
      background: var(--gold);
      margin: 24px auto 0;
    }

    .page-header h1 {
      font-family: 'Cormorant Garamond', serif;
      font-size: clamp(1.4rem, 4vw, 2.2rem);
      font-weight: 300;
      letter-spacing: 0.12em;
      color: var(--deep);
      text-transform: uppercase;
    }

    .page-header .subtitle {
      font-size: 0.9rem;
      letter-spacing: 0.25em;
      text-transform: uppercase;
      color: var(--gold);
      margin-top: 8px;
      font-weight: 500;
    }

    .page-intro {
      font-size: 1.12rem;
      font-style: italic;
      color: var(--muted);
      text-align: center;
      max-width: 700px;
      margin: 0 auto;
      padding: 20px 24px 10px;
      line-height: 1.85;
    }

    .page-content {
      max-width: 800px;
      margin: 0 auto;
      padding: 20px 24px;
    }

    .page-section {
      padding: 32px 0;
      border-bottom: 1px solid rgba(201, 150, 58, 0.15);
      opacity: 0;
      transform: translateY(20px);
      transition: opacity 0.5s ease, transform 0.5s ease;
    }

    .page-section.visible {
      opacity: 1;
      transform: translateY(0);
    }

    .page-section:last-child { border-bottom: none; }

    .page-section p {
      font-size: 1.1rem;
      line-height: 1.85;
      color: var(--text);
      margin-bottom: 14px;
    }
  </style>
</head>

<body>
  <% include partials/menu %>
    <div class="container bg-light">
      <div class="styled-page">
        <div class="page-header">
          <p class="subtitle">Music &amp; Culture</p>
          <h1>Nilkanth Pipe Band and Lazium</h1>
        </div>

        <p class="page-intro">Under the banner of SSYM, the Nilkanth Pipe Band and Lazium stand as vibrant symbols of
          cultural pride and musical excellence at our Mandir.</p>

        <div class="page-content">

          <div class="page-section">
            <p>Established in 2005 with a modest number of members playing drums and Lazium, the group has grown
              significantly alongside our expanding congregation, attracting new talent to enhance performances during
              the Mandir&rsquo;s major Utsavs.</p>
            <p>During the Mandir&rsquo;s construction phase in 2012, a group of dedicated boys began mastering their musical
              skills on recorders, later advancing to bagpipes. Their dedication intensified as they prepared for the
              Murti Pran Pratistha Mahotsav, with both the Lazium group and Pipe Band committing to regular rehearsals.
              This commitment culminated in the official launch of the Nilkanth Pipe Band during the Nilkanth Mahotsav
              &ndash; Murti Pratistha in January 2013.</p>
            <p>Today, the Nilkanth Pipe Band boasts a talented ensemble comprising 18 bagpipe players, 6 snare drum
              players, 2 bass drum players, and 4 tenor drum players. Supported by over 100 boys and girls who
              contribute to the Lazium performances at major events, the band has woven itself into the cultural fabric
              of our community.</p>
            <p>The Pipe Band takes centre stage at all major Mandir events and has collaborated with Mandirs across
              Australia for international performances. Their crowning achievement was performing with other Mandirs at
              the 200-year anniversary of Bhuj Mandir in 2023 in India. Beyond temple grounds, the band also actively
              engages in diverse community events, enriching lives with their music and spreading cultural joy far
              beyond our Mandir&rsquo;s walls.</p>
          </div>

        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

  <script>
    var observer = new IntersectionObserver(function (entries) {
      entries.forEach(function (e) {
        if (e.isIntersecting) { e.target.classList.add('visible'); observer.unobserve(e.target); }
      });
    }, { threshold: 0.15 });
    document.querySelectorAll('.page-section').forEach(function (el) { observer.observe(el); });
  </script>

  <% include partials/footer %>
</body>

</html>
